\int\frac{1}{\sqrt{x^2+25}}\,\dee{x}
&=\int \frac{1}{\sqrt{25\tan^2 u+25}}\,5\sec^2 u\,\dee{u}

&=\int \frac{5\sec^2u}{5\sec u}\,\dee{u} =\int \sec u\,\dee{u}

&= \log\big|\sec u+\tan u\big|+C

